4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would prohibit certain covered
6 entities that maintain biological data or neural data
7 from transferring or disclosing a consumer's biological
8 data or neural data to a third party without the
9 express consent of the consumer.
10 This bill would prohibit a covered entity from
11 using a consumer's biological data or neural data for a
12 purpose other than what is necessary to perform the
13 services or provide the goods requested by the
14 consumer.
15 This bill would prohibit a covered entity from
16 marketing to a consumer based on the consumer's
17 biological data or neural data.
18 This bill would require a covered entity to
19 notify a consumer before his or her biological data or
20 neural data is otherwise transferred, disclosed, or
21 used, and would provide the consumer the ability to
22 limit or prevent the transfer, disclosure, or use of
23 the data.
24 This bill would also allow the Consumer Interest
25 Division of the Office of the Attorney General to
26 enforce this act and levy a civil penalty of $3,000 per
27 violation.
